Just uploaded a new version 3 beta of [[maxi]].

Webconverger has pretty AMAZING [[i18n]] support. That means after adding a locale in the [[boot]] option [`locale=ja_JP.UTF-8`](http://flickr.com/photos/hendry/2502506953/) you get a Japanese Web kiosk. Easy.

This is great to play around with exotic [CJK](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CJK) characters and inputs. Select a text box and [scim](http://www.scim-im.org/) (an input switcher) will be activated with [Control]+[Space]. Pretty impressive huh?

# Chinese

	locale=zh_CN.UTF-8 keyb=zh

