Trouble is, I don't hear of many people from the [CJK](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CJK) part of the world. :(

The only time I heard that Chinese people love Webconverger, was from a library in Canada. Come on guys, you're **welcome on the open Web platform**. I'm happy to see many [Chinese are already using UTF-8](http://googleblog.blogspot.com/2008/05/moving-to-unicode-51.html), which is great news. If you're Asian and find the fonts or some other rendering looks bad, **please** let me know.

